description.p:
According to a first aspect of the present invention there is provided a method of controlling quality of video data transmitted from a first user terminal to at least one other user terminal in a communication system, wherein the video data is captured for transmission by a camera connected to said first user terminal, the method comprising the steps of:
detecting at said first user terminal a condition that indicates that the quality of the video data is below an acceptable threshold;
automatically generating instructions based on the detected condition for a user of the first user terminal, said instructions notifying the user of how to remedy a problem due to the detected condition and intended to provide a humanly implementable remedy to the problem to improve the quality of the video data;
outputting the instructions to the user in a humanly comprehensible form; and receiving an input from a user of the first user terminal responsive to the instructions to implement the remedy and thereby improve the quality of the video data, wherein the remedy is a physical act carried out by the user and the detected condition relates to one of:
in the case where the camera is connected to the first user terminal via a USB connection, an available bandwidth of the USB connection between the camera and the first user terminal; and
the intensity of light in the video data captured by the camera;
and the instructions output to the user comprising one of: instructions to disconnect USB devices other than said camera connected to the first user terminal;
instructions to connect the camera to the first user terminal via an alternative USB connection; and
instructions to increase the level of light input into the camera.

According to a second aspect of the present invention there is provided a user device in a communication system, said user device having means (112) for transmitting video data to at least one other device in the communication system, the video data being captured for transmission by a camera (126) connected to said user device, the user device comprising:
means for detecting a condition that indicates that video data quality is below an acceptable threshold;
means for automatically generating instructions based on the detected condition for a user of the at least one node, said instructions notifying the user of how to remedy a problem due to the detected condition and intended to provide a humanly implementable remedy to the problem to improve the video data quality;
means (130) for outputting the instructions to the user in a humanly comprehensible form; and
means for receiving input from a user of the user device responsive to the instructions to implement the remedy and thereby improve the video data quality, wherein the remedy is a physical act carried out by the user and the detected condition relates to one of:
in the case where the camera is connected to the user device via a USB connection, an available bandwidth of the USB connection between the camera and the user device; and
the intensity of light in the video data captured by the camera;
and the instructions output to the user comprising one of:
instructions to disconnect USB devices other than said camera connected to the first user terminal;
instructions to connect the camera to the first user terminal via an alternative USB connection; and
instructions to increase the level of light input into the camera.

